    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficient factor (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted under the rationale that ASTM F1717 defines a single normative test configuration and the regulatory precedent for this device class does not require multi-condition validation. All three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and <10% difference acceptance criteria across the FEA ensemble. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion for this COU.",
